{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775845077648,"sessionID":"ses_28763aefaffeXLHE2Fqv4IE2z2","part":{"id":"prt_d789d68d1001SpG6k3djyPet1P","messageID":"msg_d789d5d8d0013HubOE6sbffTv3","sessionID":"ses_28763aefaffeXLHE2Fqv4IE2z2","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_db5500065020428c85713259","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-006/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-006/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Proposal: AR-006 — Sandbox 删除与生命周期管理\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: Implement comprehensive Sandbox deletion and lifecycle management within the WorkloadManager module for the AgentCube platform. This feature ensures proper cleanup of sandbox resources, handles graceful termination, and manages the complete sandbox lifecycle from creation to destruction.\n6: \n7: The Sandbox lifecycle management provides:\n8: \n9: - **Graceful shutdown** — Proper termination of sandbox pods with configurable timeout\n10: - **Resource cleanup** — Complete removal of associated Kubernetes resources (pods, services, claims)\n11: - **Lifecycle hooks** — Pre-stop and post-start hooks for custom cleanup/setup logic\n12: - **Idle timeout management** — Automatic shutdown of idle sandboxes to conserve resources\n13: - **Finalizer-based protection** — Prevent premature deletion before cleanup completes\n14: - **Cascading deletion** — Coordinated deletion of dependent resources\n15: - **Status tracking** — Accurate lifecycle phase reporting throughout the sandbox lifetime\n16: \n17: ## Scope\n18: \n19: **Module:** `pkg/workloadmanager`  \n20: **Language:** Go  \n21: **Size:** M\n22: \n23: ### In Scope\n24: \n25: 1. **Sandbox Deletion Interface** (`pkg/workloadmanager/processor/sandbox_processor.go`)\n26:    - `Delete(ctx, sandboxName, namespace)` method\n27:    - Graceful period configuration\n28:    - Cascading deletion logic\n29:    - Finalizer management\n30: \n31: 2. **Lifecycle Manager** (`pkg/workloadmanager/processor/sandbox_lifecycle.go`)\n32:    - Phase transition management (Pending → Running → Terminating → Terminated)\n33:    - Idle timeout monitoring\n34:    - Session duration enforcement\n35:    - Lifecycle state machine\n36: \n37: 3. **Finalizer Controller** (`pkg/workloadmanager/processor/sandbox_finalizer.go`)\n38:    - Add finalizers on sandbox creation\n39:    - Remove finalizers after cleanup completes\n40:    - Prevent orphaned resources\n41: \n42: 4. **Cleanup Orchestrator** (`pkg/workloadmanager/processor/sandbox_cleanup.go`)\n43:    - Delete associated pod\n44:    - Remove services/endpoints\n45:    - Clean up SandboxClaim references\n46:    - Release resource quotas\n47: \n48: 5. **Idle Timeout Handler** (`pkg/workloadmanager/processor/idle_timeout.go`)\n49:    - Monitor last activity timestamp\n50:    - Trigger shutdown on timeout\n51:    - Configurable timeout per sandbox\n52: \n53: 6. **Integration with AgentRuntime Handler** (`pkg/workloadmanager/handler/agent_runtime.go`)\n54:    - Trigger sandbox deletion on AgentRuntime delete\n55:    - Handle cascading cleanup\n56:    - Report deletion status\n57: \n58: 7. **Integration with Sandbox Handler** (`pkg/workloadmanager/handler/sandbox.go`)\n59:    - Explicit sandbox deletion endpoint\n60:    - Force delete option\n61:    - Deletion status reporting\n62: \n63: ### Out of Scope\n64: \n65: - Garbage collection of orphaned sandboxes (separate controller responsibility)\n66: - Cross-namespace lifecycle orchestration (future enhancement)\n67: - Sandbox checkpoint/restore (deferred to persistence feature)\n68: - Multi-sandbox coordination (orchestrator feature)\n69: - Custom lifecycle policies via CRD (future enhancement)\n70: \n71: ## Impact Analysis\n72: \n73: ### Dependencies\n74: \n75: | Dependency | Type | Reason |\n76: |------------|------|--------|\n77: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` | Required | Generated Kubernetes client for AgentRuntime/Sandbox |\n78: | `k8s.io/client-go` | Required | Core Kubernetes client for Pod/Service operations |\n79: | `k8s.io/api/core/v1` | Required | Pod, Service types |\n80: | `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/api/errors` | Required | Error handling |\n81: | `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1` | Required | DeleteOptions, GracePeriodSeconds |\n82: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` | Required | AgentRuntime/Sandbox types |\n83: | `k8s.io/utils/pointer` | Optional | Pointer utilities for grace period |\n84: \n85: ### Downstream Consumers\n86: \n87: 1. **AgentRuntime Handler**: Triggers sandbox deletion on AgentRuntime deletion\n88: 2. **Sandbox Handler**: Explicit sandbox deletion via HTTP API\n89: 3. **CodeInterpreter Handler**: May use sandbox deletion for interpreter cleanup\n90: 4. **Controller (future)**: Will manage lifecycle reconciliation\n91: 5. **Resource Quota Manager**: Receives cleanup notifications for quota release\n92: 6. **Monitoring**: Observes lifecycle phase transitions\n93: \n94: ### Breaking Changes\n95: \n96: None — this is initial implementation of deletion functionality.\n97: \n98: ### Migration Path\n99: \n100: Not applicable for initial implementation. Future considerations:\n101: - Finalizer name changes (would require migration to avoid stuck sandboxes)\n102: - Grace period default changes (non-breaking but affects user experience)\n103: - Lifecycle phase enum additions (backward compatible)\n104: \n105: ## Alternatives Considered\n106: \n107: ### Alternative 1: Immediate deletion without graceful shutdown\n108: \n109: **Approach:** Delete sandbox pod immediately with `gracePeriodSeconds=0`.\n110: \n111: **Pros:**\n112: - Fastest deletion\n113: - Simplest implementation\n114: - No waiting for pod termination\n115: \n116: **Cons:**\n117: - No cleanup hooks can run\n118: - Potential data loss\n119: - Violates Kubernetes best practices\n120: - Poor user experience for stateful workloads\n121: \n122: **Decision:** Rejected. Graceful shutdown is essential for proper cleanup and data integrity.\n123: \n124: ### Alternative 2: Use Kubernetes TTL controller\n125: \n126: **Approach:** Rely on Kubernetes TTL controller for automatic cleanup.\n127: \n128: **Pros:**\n129: - Leverages built-in Kubernetes mechanism\n130: - No custom lifecycle logic needed\n131: - Standard approach for time-based cleanup\n132: \n133: **Cons:**\n134: - Requires TTL controller enabled in cluster\n135: - Less flexible for custom lifecycle rules\n136: - Doesn't support idle timeout (only age-based)\n137: - Limited control over cleanup order\n138: \n139: **Decision:** Rejected. Custom lifecycle management provides more control and doesn't require cluster-wide TTL support.\n140: \n141: ### Alternative 3: Use owner references only (no finalizers)\n142: \n143: **Approach:** Rely solely on Kubernetes owner references for cascading deletion.\n144: \n145: **Pros:**\n146: - Simpler implementation\n147: - Kubernetes handles cascading automatically\n148: - No custom finalizer logic\n149: \n150: **Cons:**\n151: - No custom cleanup logic possible\n152: - Can't enforce cleanup order\n153: - No visibility into cleanup progress\n154: - Can't prevent deletion if cleanup fails\n155: \n156: **Decision:** Rejected. Finalizers provide necessary control over cleanup process and status reporting.\n157: \n158: ### Alternative 4: Background deletion without status tracking\n159: \n160: **Approach:** Delete sandbox in background without tracking deletion status.\n161: \n162: **Pros:**\n163: - Non-blocking API response\n164: - Simpler state management\n165: - Faster HTTP response\n166: \n167: **Cons:**\n168: - No visibility into deletion progress\n169: - Can't report failures\n170: - Users can't query deletion status\n171: - Hard to debug issues\n172: \n173: **Decision:** Rejected. Status tracking is essential for user experience and debugging.\n174: \n175: ### Alternative 5: Synchronous blocking deletion\n176: \n177: **Approach:** Block HTTP response until deletion fully completes.\n178: \n179: **Pros:**\n180: - Simple semantics (request = done)\n181: - Clear success/failure indication\n182: - No polling needed\n183: \n184: **Cons:**\n185: - Slow API response (up to grace period)\n186: - Risk of HTTP timeout\n187: - Poor scalability under load\n188: - Blocks handler goroutines\n189: \n190: **Decision:** Rejected. Asynchronous deletion with status tracking provides better UX and scalability.\n191: \n192: ## Implementation Plan\n193: \n194: 1. **Extend SandboxProcessor with Delete method** (`processor/sandbox_processor.go`)\n195:    ```go\n196:    func (p *SandboxProcessor) Delete(\n197:        ctx context.Context,\n198:        sandboxName string,\n199:        namespace string,\n200:        options *DeleteOptions,\n201:    ) error\n202:    ```\n203: \n204: 2. **Implement Lifecycle Manager** (`processor/sandbox_lifecycle.go`)\n205:    - Define lifecycle phases: `Pending`, `Running`, `Idle`, `Terminating`, `Terminated`\n206:    - Implement phase transition logic\n207:    - Add phase tracking to Sandbox status\n208: \n209: 3. **Implement Finalizer Controller** (`processor/sandbox_finalizer.go`)\n210:    - Define finalizer name: `agents.x-k8s.io/sandbox-cleanup`\n211:    - Add finalizer on sandbox creation\n212:    - Remove finalizer after cleanup completes\n213: \n214: 4. **Implement Cleanup Orchestrator** (`processor/sandbox_cleanup.go`)\n215:    - Delete associated pod with graceful period\n216:    - Wait for pod termination\n217:    - Clean up services/endpoints\n218:    - Remove SandboxClaim references\n219: \n220: 5. **Implement Idle Timeout Handler** (`processor/idle_timeout.go`)\n221:    - Track last activity timestamp\n222:    - Monitor idle timeout from annotations\n223:    - Trigger automatic shutdown on timeout\n224: \n225: 6. **Add Delete endpoint to Sandbox Handler** (`handler/sandbox.go`)\n226:    - `DELETE /v1/sandboxes/{name}` endpoint\n227:    - Support force delete option\n228:    - Return deletion status\n229: \n230: 7. **Integrate with AgentRuntime deletion** (`handler/agent_runtime.go`)\n231:    - Call sandbox processor delete in `DeleteAgentRuntime`\n232:    - Handle cascading cleanup\n233:    - Report deletion progress\n234: \n235: 8. **Write Unit Tests**\n236:    - Delete method tests (success, timeout, not found)\n237:    - Lifecycle phase transition tests\n238:    - Finalizer add/remove tests\n239:    - Cleanup orchestrator tests\n240:    - Idle timeout trigger tests\n241: \n242: 9. **Write Integration Tests**\n243:    - End-to-end sandbox deletion with test K8s cluster\n244:    - Graceful shutdown verification\n245:    - Finalizer blocking behavior\n246:    - Cascading deletion verification\n247: \n248: ## Lifecycle Architecture\n249: \n250: ### Lifecycle Phases\n251: \n252: ```\n253: ┌─────────────┐\n254: │  Pending    │ ──→ Sandbox CR created, pod not yet scheduled\n255: └──────┬──────┘\n256:        │\n257:        ▼\n258: ┌─────────────┐\n259: │  Running    │ ──→ Pod is running and ready\n260: └──────┬──────┘\n261:        │\n262:        ├──────→ [Idle] ──→ No activity for idle timeout\n263:        │\n264:        ▼\n265: ┌─────────────┐\n266: │ Terminating │ ──→ Deletion initiated, finalizer present\n267: └──────┬──────┘\n268:        │\n269:        ▼\n270: ┌─────────────┐\n271: │ Terminated  │ ──→ All resources cleaned up\n272: └─────────────┘\n273: ```\n274: \n275: ### Deletion Flow\n276: \n277: 1. **User initiates deletion** (DELETE /api/v1/agentruntimes/{name})\n278: 2. **Handler calls SandboxProcessor.Delete()**\n279: 3. **Finalizer check**: If finalizer exists, proceed to cleanup\n280: 4. **Cascading deletion**:\n281:    - Send SIGTERM to pod (graceful shutdown)\n282:    - Wait for pod termination (respect grace period)\n283:    - Delete associated services/endpoints\n284:    - Remove SandboxClaim references\n285: 5. **Cleanup verification**: Confirm all resources deleted\n286: 6. **Remove finalizer**: Allow sandbox CR deletion\n287: 7. **Update status**: Set phase to `Terminated`\n288: \n289: ### Finalizer Pattern\n290: \n291: ```yaml\n292: apiVersion: agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1\n293: kind: Sandbox\n294: metadata:\n295:   name: my-runtime-abc123\n296:   namespace: default\n297:   finalizers:\n298:     - agents.x-k8s.io/sandbox-cleanup  # Blocks deletion until cleanup completes\n299: spec:\n300:   ...\n301: ```\n302: \n303: **Finalizer removal logic:**\n304: ```go\n305: // After cleanup completes\n306: sandbox.SetFinalizers(removeFinalizer(sandbox.GetFinalizers(), \"agents.x-k8s.io/sandbox-cleanup\"))\n307: userClient.Update(ctx, sandbox, metav1.UpdateOptions{})\n308: ```\n309: \n310: ### Graceful Shutdown\n311: \n312: **Default grace period:** 30 seconds\n313: \n314: **Override via annotation:**\n315: ```yaml\n316: metadata:\n317:   annotations:\n318:     runtime.agentcube.io/grace-period-seconds: \"60\"\n319: ```\n320: \n321: **Shutdown sequence:**\n322: 1. Delete pod with `GracePeriodSeconds`\n323: 2. Kubernetes sends SIGTERM\n324: 3. Pod runs pre-stop hooks (if defined)\n325: 4. Pod shuts down gracefully\n326: 5. After grace period, Kubernetes sends SIGKILL\n327: 6. Pod deleted\n328: \n329: ### Idle Timeout\n330: \n331: **Configuration:**\n332: ```yaml\n333: metadata:\n334:   annotations:\n335:     runtime.agentcube.io/idle-timeout: \"1h\"  # 1 hour idle timeout\n336: ```\n337: \n338: **Implementation:**\n339: - Track `lastActivityTime` in sandbox status\n340: - Background goroutine monitors idle timeout\n341: - Trigger deletion when `now - lastActivityTime > idleTimeout`\n342: - Update status to `Idle` before termination\n343: \n344: ## API Extension\n345: \n346: ### New Endpoints\n347: \n348: | Method | Path | Description |\n349: |--------|------|-------------|\n350: | `DELETE` | `/api/v1/agentruntimes/{name}` | Delete AgentRuntime + cascading sandbox deletion |\n351: | `DELETE` | `/v1/sandboxes/{name}` | Delete sandbox directly |\n352: | `GET` | `/v1/sandboxes/{name}/status` | Get sandbox lifecycle status |\n353: | `POST` | `/v1/sandboxes/{name}/extend` | Extend sandbox lifetime |\n354: \n355: ### Delete Request Options\n356: \n357: ```json\n358: // DELETE /v1/sandboxes/{name}?gracePeriodSeconds=30&force=false\n359: {\n360:   \"gracePeriodSeconds\": 30,  // Optional, default 30\n361:   \"force\": false             // Optional, default false\n362: }\n363: ```\n364: \n365: **Parameters:**\n366: - `gracePeriodSeconds`: Grace period for graceful shutdown (0 = immediate)\n367: - `force`: Force deletion even if cleanup fails\n368: \n369: ### Sandbox Status Response\n370: \n371: ```json\n372: {\n373:   \"name\": \"my-runtime-sandbox\",\n374:   \"namespace\": \"default\",\n375:   \"phase\": \"Terminating\",\n376:   \"podName\": \"my-runtime-sandbox-abc123\",\n377:   \"podIP\": \"10.244.1.5\",\n378:   \"startTime\": \"2026-04-11T00:00:00Z\",\n379:   \"lastActivityTime\": \"2026-04-11T01:30:00Z\",\n380:   \"idleTimeout\": \"1h\",\n381:   \"shutdownTime\": \"2026-04-11T08:00:00Z\",\n382:   \"conditions\": [\n383:     {\n384:       \"type\": \"Ready\",\n385:       \"status\": \"False\",\n386:       \"reason\": \"Terminating\",\n387:       \"message\": \"Sandbox is being terminated\",\n388:       \"lastTransitionTime\": \"2026-04-11T02:00:00Z\"\n389:     }\n390:   ],\n391:   \"finalizers\": [\"agents.x-k8s.io/sandbox-cleanup\"],\n392:   \"resources\": {\n393:     \"cpuLimit\": \"1\",\n394:     \"memoryLimit\": \"512Mi\",\n395:     \"storageLimit\": \"1Gi\"\n396:   }\n397: }\n398: ```\n399: \n400: ### Lifecycle Phase Enum\n401: \n402: ```go\n403: type SandboxPhase string\n404: \n405: const (\n406:     SandboxPhasePending    SandboxPhase = \"Pending\"\n407:     SandboxPhaseRunning    SandboxPhase = \"Running\"\n408:     SandboxPhaseIdle       SandboxPhase = \"Idle\"\n409:     SandboxPhaseTerminating SandboxPhase = \"Terminating\"\n410:     SandboxPhaseTerminated  SandboxPhase = \"Terminated\"\n411: )\n412: ```\n413: \n414: ## Success Criteria\n415: \n416: - [ ] `Delete()` method implemented in SandboxProcessor\n417: - [ ] Graceful shutdown with configurable grace period\n418: - [ ] Finalizer prevents premature sandbox deletion\n419: - [ ] Cascading deletion removes all associated resources (pod, services, claims)\n420: - [ ] Lifecycle phase tracking (Pending → Running → Idle → Terminating → Terminated)\n421: - [ ] Idle timeout monitoring and automatic shutdown\n422: - [ ] Deletion status endpoint returns accurate phase\n423: - [ ] Unit tests cover all deletion scenarios (>80% coverage)\n424: - [ ] Integration tests pass with test K8s cluster\n425: - [ ] Error handling for all failure scenarios (cleanup failure, timeout, not found)\n426: - [ ] Force delete option bypasses graceful shutdown\n427: - [ ] Finalizer removed only after cleanup completes\n428: \n429: ## Testing Strategy\n430: \n431: ### Unit Tests\n432: \n433: 1. **SandboxProcessor Delete Tests**\n434:    - Test Delete() with existing sandbox\n435:    - Test Delete() with non-existent sandbox (not found error)\n436:    - Test Delete() with graceful period\n437:    - Test Delete() with force option\n438:    - Test Delete() timeout handling\n439: \n440: 2. **Lifecycle Manager Tests**\n441:    - Test phase transitions (Pending → Running)\n442:    - Test idle detection and transition to Idle phase\n443:    - Test termination transition (Running → Terminating → Terminated)\n444:    - Test phase validation (invalid transitions rejected)\n445: \n446: 3. **Finalizer Tests**\n447:    - Test finalizer addition on sandbox creation\n448:    - Test finalizer removal after cleanup\n449:    - Test finalizer blocking behavior (deletion blocked until cleanup)\n450:    - Test multiple finalizers\n451: \n452: 4. **Cleanup Orchestrator Tests**\n453:    - Test pod deletion with graceful period\n454:    - Test service/endpoint cleanup\n455:    - Test SandboxClaim reference removal\n456:    - Test cleanup failure handling\n457: \n458: 5. **Idle Timeout Tests**\n459:    - Test idle timeout detection\n460:    - Test automatic shutdown trigger\n461:    - Test timeout configuration from annotations\n462:    - Test activity timestamp updates\n463: \n464: ### Integration Tests\n465: \n466: 1. **End-to-End Deletion Flow**\n467:    - Create sandbox via HTTP API\n468:    - Delete sandbox via HTTP API\n469:    - Verify pod deleted with graceful shutdown\n470:    - Verify finalizer removed\n471:    - Verify sandbox CR deleted\n472: \n473: 2. **Cascading Deletion**\n474:    - Create AgentRuntime with sandbox\n475:    - Delete AgentRuntime\n476:    - Verify sandbox deleted\n477:    - Verify pod deleted\n478:    - Verify all resources cleaned up\n479: \n480: 3. **Idle Timeout Flow**\n481:    - Create sandbox with idle timeout annotation\n482:    - Wait for idle timeout\n483:    - Verify automatic shutdown triggered\n484:    - Verify status updated to Idle then Terminated\n485: \n486: 4. **Force Delete**\n487:    - Create sandbox\n488:    - Delete with force=true\n489:    - Verify immediate deletion (no graceful period)\n490: \n491: 5. **Finalizer Blocking**\n492:    - Create sandbox\n493:    - Initiate deletion\n494:    - Verify sandbox stuck in Terminating (finalizer present)\n495:    - Complete cleanup manually\n496:    - Verify finalizer removed and sandbox deleted\n497: \n498: ## Risks and Mitigations\n499: \n500: | Risk | Impact | Likelihood | Mitigation |\n501: |------|--------|------------|------------|\n502: | Cleanup hangs indefinitely | High | Medium | Implement timeout for cleanup; force delete option |\n503: | Finalizer never removed | High | Low | Add finalizer removal deadline; monitoring alerts |\n504: | Pod stuck in Terminating | Medium | Medium | Force delete after grace period; SIGKILL fallback |\n505: | Resource leaks (orphaned pods) | High | Medium | Garbage collection controller (future); monitoring |\n506: | Cascading deletion order wrong | Medium | Low | Define strict deletion order; test thoroughly |\n507: | Idle timeout false positives | Medium | Low | Activity heartbeat mechanism; configurable timeout |\n508: | Force delete data loss | High | Low | Document force delete risks; require explicit flag |\n509: \n510: ## Future Considerations\n511: \n512: 1. **Garbage Collection Controller**: Background controller to clean up orphaned sandboxes\n513: 2. **Checkpoint/Restore**: Save sandbox state before deletion for later restoration\n514: 3. **Custom Lifecycle Policies**: CRD-based lifecycle configuration\n515: 4. **Multi-Sandbox Coordination**: Coordinated deletion of related sandboxes\n516: 5. **Pre-stop/Post-start Hooks**: User-defined lifecycle hooks\n517: 6. **Deletion Cost Tracking**: Track resource cost per sandbox lifetime\n518: 7. **Sandbox Archiving**: Archive sandbox logs/artifacts before deletion\n519: 8. **Deletion Policies**: Configurable policies per namespace/tenant\n520: \n521: ## References\n522: \n523: - [Kubernetes Finalizers](https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/overview/working-with-objects/finalizers/)\n524: - [Kubernetes Graceful Shutdown](https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/workloads/pods/pod-lifecycle/#pod-termination)\n525: - [Kubernetes Owner References](https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/overview/working-with-objects/owners-dependents/)\n526: - Related: `changes/AR-005/` (Sandbox 创建处理器)\n527: - Related: `deployment/client-go.md`\n528: - Related: `pkg/workloadmanager/processor/sandbox_processor.go`\n\n(End of file - total 528 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Proposal: AR-006 — Sandbox 删除与生命周期管理\n\n## Purpose\n\nImplement comprehensive Sandbox deletion and lifecycle management within the WorkloadManager module for the AgentCube platform. This feature ensures proper cleanup of sandbox resources, handles graceful termination, and manages the complete sandbox lifecycle from creation to destruction.\n\nThe Sandbox lifecycle management provides:\n\n- **Graceful shutdown** — Proper termination of sandbox pods with configurable timeout\n- **Resource cleanup** — Complete removal of associated Kubernetes resources (pods, services, claims)\n- **Lifecycle hooks** — Pre-stop and post-start hooks for custom cleanup/setup logic\n- **Idle timeout management** — Automatic shutdown of idle sandboxes to conserve resources\n- **Finalizer-based protection** — Prevent premature deletion before cleanup completes\n- **Cascading deletion** — Coordinated deletion of dependent resources\n- **Status tracking** — Accurate lifecycle phase reporting throughout the sandbox lifetime\n\n## Scope\n\n**Module:** `pkg/workloadmanager`  \n**Language:** Go  ","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-006/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775845077617,"end":1775845077645}}}}
